==English==

===Noun===
{{Wikipedia}}
'''widescreen'''

#A screen with a wider aspect ratio than the ordinary 35 millimeter frame, making more effective use of the human field of view and producing a more immersive view experience.

====Translations====
*[[Japanese]]: [[ワイドスクリーン]] (waidosukurīn)

===Adjective===
'''widescreen'''

#''Filmology.'' Filmed in a greater aspect ratio than the 1.33:1 or 1.37:1 aspect ratio.
#Presented in the original aspect ratio (of a motion picture). Presented in letterbox orientation.

